The website https://www.covid19india.org/ has a map showing the geographic distribution and graphs showing the temporal trends and epidemic curves.

According to the Worldometer population webpages, India has an estimated population of about 1.38 billion people in 2020. Before jumping in with a comment re underreporting (which is present in most countries with high case counts, one factor that may play into the reported case numbers is the statistic that the median age in India is 28.4 years. With the majority of the population falling into the age groups that have lower severe clinical disease and estimated higher asymptomatic or mild illness from infection with the SARS-CoV-2, the overall reported cases may be lower than one might have expected before looking at the population distribution (https://www.worldometers.info/world-population/india-population/). The population size, combined with the high population density, makes social distancing challenging in many locations throughout the country.

A map of India showing states and union territories can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/maps/India-States-Map.jpg, and a HealthMap/ProMED map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7486560,142. - Mod.MPP]

